1. appointment: [noun][C] an arrangement to see someone at a particular time,especailly for a business meeting or to get
                a professional service.
                       
2. apply: [verb][I] 1.to make an offical request for a job or a place in a college or university.
          request a job etc.
          affect/be relevant to
          use method/process etc
          put something on surface.
          use physical force.

3.approach: [noun][C] a particular way of thinking about or dealing with something: We need a fresh approach to sports in
            education. [+ to] He has a relaxed approach to life. [adopt/take/use an approach] As a writer she takes a 
            completely new approach to the classic horror story.
            
            
4.approach:[verb][I/T]:to move closer to someone or something: she heared footsteps approaching from behind.

5.approval:[noun][U] 1) the belief that something or someone is good or acceptable.
                     2) offical agreement or permission. given by someone in authority.
                     
6.approve:[verb] [I][never progressive] to have a positive feeling towards someone or something that you consider to be good or suitable

7.April:[noun][C/U] the fourth month of the year.
        We moved there last April.

8.area:[noun][C] (1) a particular subject,type of activity etc: Mathematics is a subject which has links with all other curriculum areas.
                 (2) a part of a city, town, country etc: Bus services in Vancouver and he surrounding area.

9.argue:[verb][I] if people argue,they speak to each other in a angry way because they disagree.

10.argument:[noun][C] an angry disagreement between people = quarrel
                      without an argument -- They won't accept higher prices without an argument.
                      have an argument(with sb) -- I've had an argument with my girlfriend.
                      
11.arise:[verb][I] if a particular situation or problem arise, It begins to exist or to develop.


12.arm:[noun][C] one of the two long parts of your body with your hands at the end: I put my arm around this shoulder.


13.army:[noun][C][often singular] a large group of soliders organized to fight battles


14.around[adv,preposition]
         As a preposition:(following by a noun) We walked around the old town.
         As a adv:(without a following group): She turned around and smile at me
         (1) used for showing movement: Moving in circular way.
         
15.arrange[verb][I/T] to make plans for something to happen, for example by agreeing a time and place.


16.arrangement:[noun][C][often plrual] a way of organizing things so that problems are solved or avoided.
               I'm staying with Sally until my heating gets fixed-it's a temporary arrangement.
               
17.arrival:[noun][U] the time when someone or something arrives at a place from somewhere else.
                     
                     
18.arrive:[verb][I] to reach a place, after having been somewhere else:
                    +at/in Four police officers suddenly arrived at their house.

19.art:[noun][U] paintings, drawings, and sculptures that a created to be beautiful or to express ideas
                 Do you like morden art?

20.article:[noun][C] a piece of writting about a particular subject that is published in newspaper or magazine:
                     He has written several articles for the Times.

21.artist:[noun][C] someone who makes paintings, sculptures etc: He had his portrait painted by the Spanish artist Daniel 


22.as:[adv,preposition,conjunction] ... To Be continued.


23.ask:[verb][I/T] to speak or write to someone in order to get information from them.


24.aspect:[noun][C] a particular part, feature, or quality of something: [+ of] a system of rules that covers almost every
                    aspect of their lives.
                    
25.assembly:[noun][U] the act of connecting together the parts of something(such as a machine)
                  [C] a group of people who make and change laws for a government or organization.
                  
26.assist[verb][I/T] to help someone or something: They eventually agree to assist rapid investigation.


27.assistance:[noun][U] help given to someone or help that allows something to be done. financial/military assistance.


28.associate:[verb][T]: to form a connection in your mind between different people for things.
                      How do humans associate these seemingly opposed ideas?
                      
29.association:[noun][C] a group of people who have joined together because they have similiar interests or aims.
                         a professional assoication of engineers 

30.assume:[verb][T] To believe that something  is true, even though no one has told you or even though you have no proof.
   
         
  
